title: Intending to Return to Afghanistan by end of 2005 and Province of Origin in Afghanistan, Afghanistan, 2005
name: Intending to Return to Afghanistan by end of 2005 and Province of Origin in Afghanistan, Afghanistan, 2005
description:
Intending to Return to Afghanistan by end of 2005 and Province of Origin in Afghanistan

Around 17% of all Afghans residing in Pakistan intend to return to Afghanistan by the end
of 2005. Province level responses from AJK (34%), Balochistan (27.6%) and Sindh
(24.5%) show a significantly higher return potential than average - when responses are
compared by percentage. Punjab and Islamabad reflect the average, whereas NWFP
returns are likely to be lower by percentage.
Intention to return by numbers (not percentages), results are dominated by NWFP. We can
anticipate that 45% (239, 748) of returns will originate from NWFP in 2005. 40% of returns
are likely to come from Balochistan, with the other 15% of returns deriving from the
remaining parts/provinces in Pakistan.
